How to create a volume in docker 

datasirpi@datasirpi-HP-Pavilion-Laptop-14-dv2xxx:~/Simplybyte_calculator$ sudo docker volume
[sudo] password for datasirpi: 
Usage:  docker volume COMMAND

Manage volumes

Commands:
  create      Create a volume
  inspect     Display detailed information on one or more volumes
  ls          List volumes
  prune       Remove unused local volumes
  rm          Remove one or more volumes

Run 'docker volume COMMAND --help' for more information on a command.
datasirpi@datasirpi-HP-Pavilion-Laptop-14-dv2xxx:~/Simplybyte_calculator$ sudo docker volume ls
DRIVER    VOLUME NAME
datasirpi@datasirpi-HP-Pavilion-Laptop-14-dv2xxx:~/Simplybyte_calculator$ sudo docker volume create data-vol
data-vol
datasirpi@datasirpi-HP-Pavilion-Laptop-14-dv2xxx:~/Simplybyte_calculator$ sudo docker volume ls
DRIVER    VOLUME NAME
local     data-vol
datasirpi@datasirpi-HP-Pavilion-Laptop-14-dv2xxx:~/Simplybyte_calculator$ sudo docker volume inspect data-vol

 sudo ls /var/lib/docker/volumes/
sudo ls -lrt /var/lib/docker/volumes/
docker ps -a
docker images
docker images ls
sudo docker run -d -it --name ubuntu1 --mount source=app_vol,destination=/data /bin/bash
